				<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="544"> 
					<tr>
						<td><b>Ingredients</b></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="10" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr>
						<td>5 Chinese cabbages (15kg), rock salts 1.5kg, water 3 L, 2 radish (3kg), 2 pears, 10 chestnuts, 5 seogi mushrooms, 10 dried jujube, spring onions  <img src="images/half.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" vspace="2">bunch (200g), watercress 1 bunch (300g), leaf mustard  <img src="images/half.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" vspace="2">bunch (500g), green onion  <img src="images/half.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" vspace="2">bunch (400g), 5 whole garlics (200g), 3 whole gingers, shredded red peppers 20g, salt-fermented shrimps  <img src="images/half.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" vspace="2">C, fine salts  <img src="images/half.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" vspace="2">C, sugar 2</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="10" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>TbspKimchi liquid : water 4 L, salt  <img src="images/half32.gif" border="0" align="absmiddle" vspace="2">C</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="20" border="0"></td></tr>
				</table>
				
				<!-- -->
				<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="544"> 
					<tr>
						<td colspan="2"><b>Directions</b></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="10" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td width="15">1)</td>
						<td>Cut the Chinese cabbage into 4 pieces, salt down in 9% salt water, drain, wash, and remove the roots.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>2)</td>
						<td>Shred the radish into strips.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>3)</td>
						<td>Trim the spring onions, water cresss, and leaf mustard. Cut them into 4cm -long strips. Cut only the white part of large green onions diagonally into strips.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>4)</td>
						<td>Shred the ginger and garlic into strips. Mince the solids of salt-fermented shrimps.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>5)</td>
						<td>Pit and shred the dried jujube. Cut the pears, chestnuts, pyogo mushrooms, seogi mushroom into strips, and cut the shredded red peppers in 3cm length.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>6)</td>
						<td>In a large bowl, combine shredded radish, pear, chestnuts, and jujube with red peppers, so that the ingredients are tinged with red color. Add watercress, 
							leaf mustard, spring onions, green onions, garlic, ginger, seogi, pyogo, and salt-fermented shrimps and mix well. Season with liquid of salt-fermented shrimps.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>7)</td>
						<td>Place a small amount of mixed ingredients between leaves of salted Chinese cabbage evenly, wrap it with the biggest leaf to keep ingredients from falling, and put it in an earthenware Kimchi pot.</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>8)</td>
						<td>For Kimchi juice, make salt water and pour enough to cover the top of Kimchi.</td>
					</tr>
